\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid2912712 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What is your marital status? You are a widow, aren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The year when you were married was ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And the year when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 1887.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose}, the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Channing Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you remember how long you lived in that house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, I was about .
.. let me see, I should think about 11. I started to work when I was 11, but we moved out of that house, you know, directly when I went to work you see, and we went to live in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street
}}Burlington Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} when I was about 11. It was a bigger house and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Burlington Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 when you were about 11?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Because it was a bigger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, and we had a family growing up, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, 'till I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you tell me how many brothers and sisters you had and what order they came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes. I had 5 brothers and 1 sister. But the eldest one, the one that was born first, she died, but I don't know anything about her, you see. She was the first child that was born to me mother and father, and she died w
hen she was a baby, I suppose, I don't know. Then I had 4 brothers older than me, and one younger, and a sister older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Four brothers and another sister older than you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, and one brother younger. That was 7 of us, altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did the one sister come after the 4 brothers, or in between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, she came ... the eldest, then the next one, then the next one. She were the fourth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you mean the fourth out of the ones that lived or the fourth of the whole lot?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Fourth
 of the ones that lived. See, I can't remember anything about that, only I heard them talking about it, you see, about the first one. I don't know anything about her, only that she died. That's all I know, you see, when she was a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you know how much time elapsed between each of the members of the family being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, I should think about two years. Two years, you know, generally had them two years and over. But between me and the next eldest brother there were only 18 months, and then t
he next one younger than me there's 5 years, see. Five years between me and the next one to me younger. I was next to the youngest, I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But as far as the others were concerned you'd think it would be about 2 years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, every two years. I hea
rd me mother say, you know, that they had them about every two years at that time, it was supposed to be ... like, you know, what they did in those days, have them every two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I couldn
't tell you that, but I can remember him when he was 50 and it would be - oh, well, I can remember him quite well before he gave over working. He was a cotton spinner and he gave over working when he was 50. Well, I can remember him before that, he used t
o
 mend out shoes and that, you know, and I used to sit beside him and help him. See, I couldn't tell you how old he was. I can remember him from ... giving up his job, he was a cotton spinner and he went insurance agent when he was 50. And he lived 'till h
e were 87, that's 37 years that I can remember quite clear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How old were you when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I was about 40 ... 44.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 That gives us enough to give us an approximate date. He was a cotton spinner and then at 50 he became an insurance agent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he have any other jobs at all, say, before he was a cotton spinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, not that I know of, He was, like, officer at the spinners' office. He went all through the spinners' union or what it was, all through the office ... well, from the bottom to the top before he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 He was employed by the union, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, I don't know whether he got paid for it or not, but he was in the spinners' union on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}St. George's Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, but where he worked was Cross }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362178 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  Winkworth. Well, he was 
what they call the ... like, the foreman in the works, but he was ... used to keep all the books and everything, you see, from the spinners' office ... the spinners' union. Kept all the books, and he did that until he retired at 50. I don't know whether h
e got paid for it or not, I've no idea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 He was an official at the Spinners' {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, he was an official at the Spinners' Hall, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
St. George's Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, for the mill where he worked at. He was the one that used to collect the money and book it and all that for the union ... Spinners' office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he do any other part time or casual work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, just did the insurance agent ... he bought a book, you see, and just did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you remember whether he was ever out of work when you were ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Not that I know of, no. Apart from his giving up the cotton spinning and buying this book, you know, just in between, that was all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 There was a short gap in between, was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, 'till he bought the book, but I wasn't much. Can't remember him out of work at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She was younger than me father, about two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, I see. Where did she come from? Was she a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Incidentally, was your father a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your mother have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
I think she worked in the mill, too, before she was married. But after she was married she gave it up. She didn't work after she was married at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In spinning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, in the cotton spinning. Yes, they used to take women then, you know. Well, she was in that then ... I think that's where she met me father, tell you the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And she didn't work at all after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I'd like to as
k you a bit about your life at home when you were a child up to the time when you left school. First of all I've got to ask you just one question about the house you lived in. You lived at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Channing St.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} until you were 11.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, number 21.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Now, can you tell me how many rooms there were in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Only 4, 2 up and 2 down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What were they? There were two bedrooms upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did you call them? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 Living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  and kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 Living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  and scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would anyone else at all besides your mother and father and you and your brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your mother have anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, she just had one washerwoman, used to come in every Tuesday. A washerwoman, to help with the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She didn't have anyone else, apart from the washerwoman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your mother used to make or mend any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, she used to make their shirts, and she 
used to do a lot of sewing. Make curtains, bedshirts and all that, you know. Used to bake all their own bread, and all their own dinners, I never remember her buying one dinner. Make all their own dinners, and everything homemade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were there every some clothes that you would buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, we used to buy coats, you know. Coats ... costumes, we used to call them then, and we used to buy those. But she used to make all her underwear and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Where would she go to to buy your coats and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, we used to go to the Co-Op, it just started on then, you know. Just started.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she ever buy any clothes from anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, she used to go to that shop in ... there was that shop in Market Street at the end ... Deale's, she used to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And she would mend her clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, she used to mend and knit, and all that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 About how often would you get new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We used to reckon to have them every year for the sermons. A frock and shoes 
and stockings and that ... new rig-out for the sermons. We used to go to Sunday School every Sunday, used to go 3 times. Three times every Sunday we had to go ... well, with sermons, you see. She used to buy us new clothes on sermons Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And in the main that would be when you got your new clothes, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And they would last ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Last 12 months, and then ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would the clothes that she bought you always be new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes. Used to buy us good clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And with shoes, you say your father would sometimes mend the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, used to have a big box with a hammer in and nails and everything. Used to mend the shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he ever make any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no, never made any. Just mended them, you know, when they was getting done he used to put leather on the bottom, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you used to go to the Co-Op to buy shoes, or did you used to go somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I suppose so, I can't remember that, now. I suppose it would be the Co-Op if they sold shoes then, b
ecause she was a big Co-Op woman, tell you the truth. Me father too. It was just starting up then, you see, about that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And would you have new shoes also once a year, or more frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. No, when we needed them. She used to keep us well up in clothes and shoes and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Incidentally, was it shoes, or was it clogs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, well, boys used to wear clogs. Yes, the boys used to wear clogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you remember whether your father ever used to help your mother in the house 
with things like washing up, or cooking, or cleaning, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
I don't know. He used to do his share, I suppose, but you see, we had all these lads growing up, they used to have to help. You see, we all had certain jobs that we had to d
o. Every week, you see, we had to ... one had to ... I had to ... we had a stool, and all the things in the scullery that wanted scrubbing, I used to have to do that. And me sister used to have to do all the fireplace, you see. And then me brothers, they 
used to what they call mangle for her, when she washed they'd mangle the clothes. One had to do the windows. You see, we all had different jobs that we did in the house every week..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was this sort of carrying on through the week, or was there one special day in the week when you did your chores.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, when she did the washing, you see, I used to scrub the things in the scullery, and then at the weekend, me sister - twice a week she used to do the hearth and the ... we had fire irons, you know, old 
- fashioned things we had, she used to do those twice a week. Mother used to wipe it down, you know, but she used to do it proper, what we call doing it proper twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you remember whether your father ever did anything like making the fire, for instance, or decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Oh, he used to light the fire, but no decorating. We used to have ... see, it were rented house, you see. Although, we had ... he bought two, they saved up ... for all that family they saved up and we had two houses, read
y money, money down and that was, you know, their hobby, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 As well as the one you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes. But it was a rented house, what we lived in. But they bought two. They were building a row of houses not far away and so it seemed the custom th
en, you know, neighbours, they were buying them, see. You could buy them one at a time. Well, they bought two. Ready money, I always remember it (laughter). And the man that built them said if they could pay ready money for 2, they could afford to pay for
 4, you know, like paying so much down, I suppose, and then the other yearly, monthly, what they did. But I always remember that because I used to go and collect the rents when I got a bit older, you see, that was my job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 That was one of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, I used to go and collect the rents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you remember if your father every did anything with you children, like dressing, or undressing, or bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Not that I know of. I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he read to you, or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Oh, he used to read a lot. He was a good writer, too. A lovely writer. He used to have this ... the Spinners' Hall, you know, he used to do a lot of books, and that. Well, he was a good writer. I don't think he read us stories, no. We were all readers, yo
u know. We were all readers. I am yet. I like reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he ever take you out without your mother being there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, he used to take us out every Sunday morning. The young ones. It was a ride and a walk in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Take you a ride on a bus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, well tram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would your father look after you while your mother went out? Did she used to go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She used to go out ... When they went out ... together, always. Yes, they used to go out together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she ever go out on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Only errands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 These various jobs that you had to do, did you carry on doing those all the time that you were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 After you left school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did the older children have to help the younger ones with things that the younger ones would find difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, I don't think so. Well, they must have done, but all I can remember about the older ones, they were going out, you know. Lads, they'd go out playing football and all that kind of thing, you know. They used to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Of course, there'd be quite a time lapse, really, wouldn't there, between you and your older brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Me eldest brother, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you younger children have to do anything to help the older ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time? When you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, at night. Yes, we used to go to bed. Well, I don't know, I suppose we used to play, and that, and then come in and go to bed. You know, just natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 About what time would it be, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, I should think 9 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was it your mother that used to put you to bed, or ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to go to bed ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But I mean when you were very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 When we were very young I suppose she would do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It wouldn't be your older sister, for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No. she wasn't so much ... there wasn't so much difference in our ages, you see, she was ... there were 18 month between me and the next boy elder, and then there was her. She 
was two years ... about 3 years, you see, older than me. Just above 3 years, but she wasn't that much older. In fact, I were always bigger than her, you know, she was rather small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you used to share the bedroom, or the bed, with ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, we used to sleep together, me and me sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Your older sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Of course, that was the only sister you'd got, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you had 2 bedrooms at this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How were the bedrooms allocated then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 O
h, all the boys slept in one room, and me and me sister slept where me mother and father slept, you see, in that room. That's all I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You wouldn't have a bathroom, obviously, in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No bathroom, no. We had a tin bath ... aluminium one, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Your mother, I suppose, it would be that would get the bath out. Where would you use it, in the scullery or the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You had to go out while the others had a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 , was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And what were the arrangements, did you have baths on different nights, or ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, we used to ... they used to know, you know, me mother used to say 'well, you'll have to go out 'till they've had a bath'. Just like that. And we used to go out, you see, 'till they'd had a bath (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How often did you used to get one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, only about once a week, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And it would be staggered through the week for the different members of the household, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. Well, the la
ds used to have it when the wanted, used to go to the baths, you know. The lads used to go to the baths more than what we did. And they used to go when they wanted, you see, swimming. They were all swimmers. Used to go swimming a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Your mother did the washing every week with the washerwoman. Does that mean you would have clean clothes to put on once a week or ...?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They used to change us, yes. They used to change us every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Just once every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Which room did you have your meals in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 . 'Course, they were big rooms then, you see, big places. Bigger than what they are now, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were there ever any occasions when you'd eat anywhere else? You'd only have the scullery, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We didn't used to eat in the scullery at all. The sink was in there, you see, and the boiler. The big boiler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The wash boiler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Where did your mother do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In the scullery. We had a' oven in the fireplace. Used to get it ready and put it in the oven.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You wouldn't have a gas cooker, or anything like that, of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
About what time in the morning did you used to have breakfast when you were a child? Would it be tied up with the time when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Used to have to get up about 8 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Which members of the family would be present for breakfast at the time you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, we used to all sit together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You all had your breakfast together, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I wondered if maybe some of the older ones would have gone to work first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Those that went to work used to get up and go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they get their own breakfast ready or did your mother get up ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, Mother up with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of a breakfast was it normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Used to have porridge, I know that. We didn't have egg and bacon so much, we used to have porridge more than anything, and bread, you know. Perhaps an egg divided between us, something like that. You know, it was divided, we didn'
t have egg and bacon each. Used to have it divided on our plate, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 If you had egg divided was it divided one in between two of you, or more than two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She used to do so many and put bacon in and delve it out with us all round. We used to h
ave enough, after porridge, you know, we used to have enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would you have your egg and bacon on any day of the week, or was it reserved, say, for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Once or twice, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have anything special for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, not
 ... no. We used to go to school. And we used to have a good dinner, always roast, you know, roast meat and all that at Sundays. Always had a good dinner on a Sunday. We had a good dinner any day, she was a good cook.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have meat every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Oh, yes! We used to have stewed steak and we used to have pork ribs, and we used to have ... oh, pork ribs and stewing steak ... oh, I can't tell you. Pie meat, and liver, and all that. Always a roast, a big roast about ... oh, I don't know how many lbs
. Five lbs. at least. And that was it, you see, she used to buy big portions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would she make a pudding for your dinner, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, used to have rice puddings and we used to have ... you know, pie. Make a lot of pie, meat pies and apple pies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did you do at teatimes? What did you have at teatimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
We used to have a lot of fish at one time, you know, about 3 times. 'Cos fish was cheap then. Used to have it and she used to divide it out, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 So it was like a high tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, they call it high tea now, but we just used to call it our tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What I mean is you had a substantial meal, not just a sort of bread-and-jam-tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we never had bread and jam. We had jam if we wanted it, but we didn't have that just special, like, you know, for our tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did you have to drink, by the way? Was it tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, me mother used to ... used to have plenty of milk, you know, and she used to put water in it. Milk and water. We used to drink that, was our drink at dinnertime. Always milk and water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did you drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, we'd have tea. And at teatime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Tea at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have anything just before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I can't remember. Don't think so. We'd have a drink, a drink of milk. Used to have plenty of milk going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 About what time would you have your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, about half past 5.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 After your father had come home from work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 After he'd come home from work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Now, your mother did a lot of baking? Bread and ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Bread and cakes and pies, all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she used to make jam, or bottle fruit, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Sometimes, yes, sometimes, but not often. We weren't big jam eaters at all. In fact I don't no
w. I don't care for jam, so much. I can't remember her even, you know, saying 'will you have jam' or anything like that. No, just ... if we wanted it we could have it, but we weren't jam eaters at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she used to make any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. Onion and cucumber. Used to cut the onions up and put them in vinegar and put cucumber in vinegar. Mixed pickle we used to call it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she ever make any wine? Herb wine, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. We used to buy herb beer, they used to come round with stone bottles, you know, so we used to buy herb beer. Lads used to drink that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she or your father ever make any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your mother ever used to concoct any medicine? You know how they used to have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 chamomile}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 chamomile}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  flowers and treacle, and when we had a cough ... chest ... treacle and butter and vinegar, and things like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She had a few home-made cures of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were you able to grow any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. no garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 So you would buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Buy everything like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would it be from the market, or a cart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to have the greengrocer's not far away and we used to go up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would it always be fresh fruit and vegetables, or would it sometimes be tinned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no, we used to have the fresh fruit and fresh vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you ever remember having tinned fruit, or anything, at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, they didn't believe in it, you know. Didn't believe in tinned fruit then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The next question says 'did they keep any livestock for the family, like ducks, pigs or goats'?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you ever get any extra meat, such as rabbit, as a result of somebody poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you remember ever seeing your mother have less food so that the rest of the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She never went short?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, her never went short of food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your father have more? Bigger portions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, he wasn't a big eater, me Dad, he was just ordinary .. In fact
 me mother used to try and make him eat more, but he always believed in finishing before he were full, you know, so he could eat a bit more but he wouldn't do. He believed that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were you allowed to talk during the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Allowed to talk? Oh, yes. Talk about football, lads did, more than anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you younger children could talk as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what had been cooked, or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, you know, I suppose we had it, you know, because it was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 If there was something that you didn't like, did you have to have it just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, there's only one thing I didn't like and that was cheese. I wouldn't have cheese, but we had ...
 you know, we had everything. We'd eat everything anyhow, we didn't used to leave much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What was your parents' attitude if you did leave anything uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, they'd think you weren't so well, or something like that. They'd think you was ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They didn't make you eat everything up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
If there was something on the table that you wanted, say the salt, could you ask for it to be passed to you or did you have to wait for it to go the rounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to ask for it. Yes, we used to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Could you ask for second helpings, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, if there was any left (laughter).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to used a spoon more than anything. Fork and a spoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would you have to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they tell you to sit up straight, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Used to have a big extension table, you know,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you all have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, I don't think so, I can'
t remember being tied to one place. No, I can't remember that. We used to sit down. I suppose we did, but I can't remember one particular place that I had to sit in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Could you bring toys or a book up to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no, not at mealtimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about leaving the table? When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, we used to ... we didn't used to have to ask, we used to get up and go. But when there's such a lot of you like that, you know, some eat more than others, some take long
er, and we used to get up and go, you see ... say, 'have you finished' ... and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have to wait for your mother or father asking you if you'd finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to say we were finished, and 'all right', you know ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was it your mother who }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 served}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  out the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would she carve the meat, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she have a particular order of serving you? Would she, say, serve your father first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I suppose he would be served first, but they didn't 
go, like, in rotation like that, you know. Those that sat down there were served, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I see, so it was 'first come first served'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. It wasn't, like, because they were the eldest they were served the first. It wasn't like that, at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 When you were too young to sit up to the table did you have a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't know, I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You couldn't remember about your younger brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 There's only one younger than me, you see. I can't remember much about him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 When this washerwoman came on Tuesday, did she used to come for all day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she used to eat with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, they used to have theirs first, before we came home from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Her and your mother, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, used to have theirs first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And it would be the same as you would eat when you got home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of a woman was your mother? Was she a motherly sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. She had golden hair. Dr. Gilpatrick, that was always our family doctor, used to say 'the nicest head of hair in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose}
'. He used to admire her, she had lovely hair. Beautiful. And it always ... a lot. Always a lot, you know, it never seemed to ... except when she had it ... when it was fashion to be bobbed, you know, and s
he had it cut off, you know. Dr. Gilpatrick, you know, nearly went mad. Whatever have you done that for?' he said. But she didn't look as nice after. She had beautiful hair ... like, a bit wavy and all frizzy all here, you know. And it went white just her
e. I can still remember all the white curls. She was a nice woman ... nice looking woman, fresh complexion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was she an easy person for you to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you feel sort of close to her and able to confide in her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, yes
. We had a happy home, same as ... You know, a lot of children, you know, they used to take us away every year, the whole lot of us. We used to go together, always on holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 If you felt worried about anything when you were a child did you feel that you could talk to her about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about your father, did you feel ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, he was always on the quiet side, me father. A bit on the quiet side. He used to listen to you, and all that, but not like me mother, you see. He was more
 studious and ... I suppose he'd been better educated than me mother, I don't know, but he were always like that, you know, reading and educating ... always books of some kind or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, well, we had to mind our manners, you know, yes. We daren't cheek them like they do now, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have to behave towards your brothers and sister in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, we hadn't to do any falling out ... what we used to call falling out. We weren't allowed to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And did it always work that you didn't (laughter)?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I suppose we used to ... But I can't remember ever having, like, a fight or a quarrel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It was a peaceful family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. Well, we were brought up at S
unday School and we used to go during the week as well, at night, Band of Hope and ... you know, Guild of Help and things like that we used to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents ever say that you should hit back if another child hit you, or ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I dare say, yes, don't be soft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They would encourage you to stand on your own feet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, stand up for yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What kind of people do you think that your parents hoped that you would be when you grew up? Did they bring you up to consider that certai
n things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
They used to ... you know, look after us and to get what we wanted, more or less ... never no fixed ideas about what we had to be or anything, I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But did they instill a particular sense of values in you about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, no. There were so many of us, I should think we just grew up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But they encouraged you to go to Church and Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did they think about people swearing, for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, never swore. Never heard me father swear in his life. Never used to swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did they think about other people doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I gather you were allowed to join in conversations when the grown-ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, if we'd anything to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You weren't brought up in a 'little girls had to be seen and not heard' sort of idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We'd get a smack, or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was a smack the normal kind of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, no, we didn't used to have it so often, but you had to do something wrong if you did get one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they have any other sorts of punishment like sending you to bed, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you remember any particular occasion when you were punished? And what it was for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, I can't remember anything like that. I can't remember ... I don't think me father ever hit any of us. He was on the quiet side, you see. Me mother used to tell us, like, you
 know, tell us what we had to do, behave ourselves and all like that. He put a word in now and then, but he never hit any of us. Don't remember him hitting any of us, all 7 of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would your mother perhaps tell you off if you did something, rather than inflict any punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Would you say that you got your ideas of how to behave from both your mother and your father, or did your mother play a more important part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. Well, I should think so. I think she had the ... you know, the
 most dealings with us, you know, keep them in order. 'Course, me father used to step in if we went to fight, you know what lads are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would he, perhaps, have more to do with disciplining the boys rather than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 When you had a birthday would it be different from an ordinary day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we didn't used to bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have presents or anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Didn't used to bother about birthdays. Used to know it was your birthday and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about Christmas, what happened at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, we used to have parties at Christmas. Have turkey, and all that. Plum pudding, and house decorated. Used to have singsongs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have any guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we didn't have many guests. Perhaps we'd have
 me father's sister, she was a widow, but we didn't have any outsiders, you know, we used to have a singsong among ourselves, and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would you go to Church on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, Christmas morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And then you'd come home and have your Christmas dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Used to go carol singing sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 On Christmas Day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 On Christmas Eve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We had an organ. Had one of those organs. It was a nice organ, and me brother had 
a violin, me eldest brother, and I think me next to the eldest he had one of those ... you know, concertinas. He had one of those. That was all. Then me sister was a singer. She was in the choir and I was in the choir, and that was it, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did anybody else sing beside you two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Sing? No. Well, they used to join in, but we was in the choir, you see, at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you would have a musical get-together at Christmas, and what about other times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, when we grew up, you see, we used 
to have this organ, and we lived in Burlington Street then, that was when we got older, and me brother he had a friend that was a good piano player and he used to come in with me brother after the ... they used to go to the Chapel - and they used to have 
singsongs, hymns, round the organ, all the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 On a Sunday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Sunday evening, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Ludo and dominoes and drafts, I remember drafts, and ping pong. We had a ping pong net and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they play any outdoor games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Now, you had books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, me father used to read about Gladstone and Pitt and all these ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Political men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Political men. 'Life of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Gladstone{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
', I always remember that one, and Life of .... somebody else, I forget now who it was. Was it Thomas Warr, or somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Thomas Moore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Moore{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
? Oh, it ... no there was one wall Warr, wasn't there, or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Waugh, do you mean, that Waugh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was it just your father who have books?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, I used to read. I used to read a lot. I used to read these books, sometimes, that he had, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 So you had classics like 'War and Peace', as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, we used to have The Evening News and The Guardian, The Bolton Guardian ... Bolton papers always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The Guardian once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, that's right, yes. And The Evening News. We didn't have any morning papers
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have any magazines at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You remember your father reading quite a lot, but not your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, she didn't. She used to read the papers, but not books. I can't remember her reading a book at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And they neither of them read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you remember there ever being a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, me brother. Oh, well ... We buried a brother, he was 40 when he died. That was the only one in the family that died young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
That was the next one to me, like, you know. There was the youngest brother and then there was me, and then there was this one, he went to the war. He was called up in 1914 and he was in what we call Royal Air 
Force, that one was, but he was a tailor; and he got a germ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was this after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, he died, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 So there wasn't a funeral in the family earlier than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Continuing when you were still a child, were you taken out to visit either neighbours of friends or relatives at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were you taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, used to go with me mother shopping, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you would sometimes go out just with your father, I think you said?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, on a Sunday. Always on a Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was this before or after you'd been to Church or Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, well, that was before we used to go, you know, on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I see, that was when you were very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Very young, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you used to have outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Oh, yes. They used to take us out. We used to go to .... I can remember one time when we were young, very young, just going to Windermere. I can just remember sailing on the lake ... {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
PlaceName}}Windermere{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Lake{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. I don't know how old I was, I must have been very young because we was all there. You know, they used to take us out like that, altogether. To 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose}; Southport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would this be the weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, Sunday ... well, Saturdays and Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 About how often would they be able to take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, well, you know, more like holiday times than anything, when he wasn't working, you see, when me Dad wasn't working, was on holiday.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you go away to stay for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, used to take us to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose}
 once a year, used to go for a holiday. He only had ... didn't have a week then, the cotton spinners, they only used to have Monday to Thursday, I think, four days. Yes, we used to have 4 days and we used to go for that 4 days. Used to go on the Saturday 
'till they went to work on the Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did all the children, everybody, go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The family. Well, when they was younger we went, until they wanted to go on their own, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, when they wanted to go on their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of things did you do in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose} in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Used to play ... I can remember they had a cellar where we used to stay and we had to go down in this cellar if it was raining, we had to play down in this cellar, you see, and we used to h
ave to go down to clean our shoes and we used to ... when it wasn't raining we used to go on the sand, you see, play in the water and all that kind of thing. But I always remember this cellar. Isn't it queer that I should remember this cellar? It was in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Adelaide Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose}
, and we had to go down in this cellar if it was raining. And we had to go down to clean out shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You always went to this same place every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. Mrs. Moorhouse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you used to spend your Saturdays? Was that one of the days you did your chores, your household chores? Or was it a leisure day?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Used to play, used to go out playing. We had a park not far off, you see, we used to play in this part oftener than not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And on Sundays you went to - what was it? - Church in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Chapel, we used to go ... they had a class, you know, primary ... children's I don't know what they called it then, but the youngest, you know, we used to go all in one room and the teacher used to teach us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And was it the same in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
In the afternoon we had separate classes because there used to be more of us, you see. Separate classes. And then at night is was service, a service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The ordinary evening service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents attend, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, but not every week, you know, like we did, they used to go special occasions, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Weslyan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You had different clothes for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents allow you to play games at all on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes. Yes, we used to play. We used to go in the park a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They didn't think then that it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no, we used to play games just like any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did they think about working on a Sunday? Did they think it was wrong to work on a Sunday? Or did they not seem to bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Me mother used to have to work, and that was it. None of us bothered about work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You went to the Band of Hope, and you said yo
u were in the choir. What sort of activities did these things have? Did the Band of Hope have any social activities, for instance, or The Guild of Help that you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, we used to ... The Band of Hope, no, it was just a service ... drink and 
all that, telling you about drink. We used to go Mondays, that one. And this Guild of Help was Wednesdays, I think. Well, they used to have a meeting and then occasionally at weekends they used to have what they call a ramble out in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was this an organization for young people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did the Sunday School organize any outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well that was it, you see, they all belonged to the Sunday School. I shouldn't've said the Guild of Help, it was ... The Wesley Guild I should have called it. It was called Wesley Guild, not The Guild of Help. I got that wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And this was a social thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did the choir have any social activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, we used to go out, yes. Used to have outings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Fairly often or was it once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Twice a year in the summer, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were there any other organizations in the Chapel that you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was the habit in your family to say Grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. There used to be concerts, you know, belongin
g to the Sunday School. Concerts, social evenings and all that. We used to have them pretty often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you actually take part in any of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And sometimes you went to watch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you ever have family prayers at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We had to say our prayers at night when we went to bed, but we didn't have it round the table, or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, yes, he was a Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Have you any idea why it was that he was Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She was a Liberal, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Can you remember them voting in the elections? The first time that women could vote was in 1918, can you remember whether your mother and father voted then and whether your father voted ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, I think they did. I think me mother did. They used to go together, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they always vote Liberal, or did they change at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. No, they never changed, always Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In some places at
 that time men used to think they'd risk losing their job or their house if they voted differently from either their employer or the landlord, as the case may be. Do you know if your father ever felt under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was your father actually a member of the Liberal Party in the sense of being active in its local activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, he used to go to the meetings and he used to canvass for them. Canvass for them, you know, at the elections.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he do anything other than at election time, apart from going to meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about your mother, did she take any active part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, she didn't. She used to go with me father, but she didn't used to have any active part in politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But she was interested enough to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Vote, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
When your parents weren't doing their work how did they spend their time? You've said that your mother used to do a lot of darning and things like that, and your father did a lot of reading, did they do anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, they didn't used to go out much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your mother have any interests outside the home that you know of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Not that I know of, no. I don't remember her going to any meetings of any kind or nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about the Co-Op? She was interested in the Co-Op?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, she used to go ... shop there, but she never went ... she wasn't in ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She wasn't in the Guild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you say that she didn't go out to enjoy herself except when she went with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Your father would get home from work at about...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Half past 5. Well, we didn't live far away from the mill so it would be about a quarter to six, I should think, when he got home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, he didn't used to go out }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 normally}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 , he didn't used to go out at night, he used to stay in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Except when he was canvassing at election time, or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Except when there was something special on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about the union, did that take his time in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, they used to have meetings, yes, they used to have meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he ever attend any club, or pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't know. Oh, he used to have a drink sometim
es, but nearer home, like, you know. Near home at the pub. But no club, there were no clubs then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would he go to the pub ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Perhaps me mother would go with him sometimes on a weekend, Saturday or Sunday, just for an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It was just once a week, or something like that was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, yes. At weekends, Saturdays or Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your father ever take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Not that I know of. Bowling, oh, he used to go bowling. He won a lot of prizes bowling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he ever attend races, or bet, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you remember your father and mother belonging to any sort of savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Only the Co-Op, they used to save up in the Co-Op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You mean the dividend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They didn't contribute to a sickness scheme, or a funeral scheme or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, no. Oh, insurance, they used to have insurance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was that before your father took over the agency as well, or just when we took over the agency?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, well, they a
lways had insurance, you know, like. Each one of us was insured when we was young. When we was born, even. We all had ... a penny, they used to be a penny and they used to rise, twopence, and that. Well, we all had that, one each. And when he bought this 
book for insurance, of course, got more business, like, you know, we used to join him, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Coming back to you, again, now, how did you get on you're your brothers and sisters? Was there any particular one that you felt specially close to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I
 had me eldest brother, he used to take me out a lot. He didn't get married 'till he was ... oh, quite old, me eldest brother, and he used to take me out to concerts and ... He used to take me out a lot. The Albert Hall in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} they used to have concerts there, and amateur operatic societies, they used to have operas there, you know and I used to go with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 About how old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, I don't know how old I would be, I wasn't so old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You were still a child, were you, then, or were you a young woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, perhaps about 12 or 13, something like that. And he used to be in the gymnasium a lot, athlete, you know, he used to ... well, he was a member, and it was was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Adelaide Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and it was a gymnasium club. Oh, it was going a
 long time. Well, they used to give displays, you know, at different places and we used to go. He was a good athlete. Then me and me sister joined the gymnasium when we was young. He got us to go, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 When you were very young, who did you used to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
We used to have children in the street, you know. Used to play in the street a lot more than they do now. We used to play at rope, and hopflag, and jacks, and all that kind of thing, I can remember them. You won't remember them, will you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, but I've been told about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
We used to play in the street a lot more then, we used to have a rope right across the street, you know, and jumping. Oh, it were nice. We used to pass our time a lot outside, I don't know whether we had bette
r weather or what, but we always seemed to be playing outside, at something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you ever play in other children's homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we didn't go in their houses much, no, we used to ... always outside or going in the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you play in the yard, or was it not big enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, it wasn't so big. No, we didn't used to play in the yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did your mother say if you got dirty when you were playing? Did she bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, I don't suppose ... she used to have to change us. No, she didn't used to bother, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Were you free to play with any children that you wanted to? You weren't discouraged from playing with any particular children, particular families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, they were all a decent lot down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You joined the gymnasium a
nd you belonged to these various Church groups, was there any other sort of youth organization or youth activity that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to pass all our time away at school, someway or other. Used to have bazaars and Floor shows and ... yo
u know, something going on all the time. We had a pierrot troupe one time. I was in that. We kept that up a few years. Every bazaar we had that going.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have any particular hobbies? Collecting anything, or keeping pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Used to knit and crochet and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you ever go out for walks, or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, we used to go for walks. Never had a bicycle. We used to go round what we call {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Green Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} now. There was no houses then, and we used to go right up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lever Edge Lane{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} and walk back down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Green Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, you see after Chapel on a Sunday. That were our walk always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, they used to go fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Apart from your athletics at the gymnasium did you take part in any other sort of sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, only what we did at the ... children, like, you know, and we used to play all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But not so-called sports like tennis? Or hockey, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. Used to play shuttle-cock and ping-pong, that was the nearest we got to tennis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you follow in your father's footsteps and do any bowling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. I had a brother that did. Two brothers that used to go bowling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you go to theatres at all, as well as concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, went to the theatres.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you remember what sort of things you would go to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Used to go to operas. I can remember Lucia de Lammemour, I can remember that plain enough, when I was young because you stand up ... you know, stood up when it was over, clapping. I
 always remember that. We didn't go to plays much, always musical comedies or opera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was there such a thing as a music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Used to be grand theatre, The Grand Theatre, and there used to be a Theatre Royal, both next to each other, they're both
 pulled down now. The Albert Hall used to have the concerts. Victoria Hall, used to have concerts there. It used to be twopence to go there. Saturday nights we used to go there. Used to have twopenny concerts, they used to be good, too. And then they went
 up to sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about the cinema, had cinema started then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, they were nothing like they are now. Temperance Hall was the first one, I think. It's the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Rialto{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you ever go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I went, yes, Magic }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 Lanterns}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, used to have pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you remember how much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No (laughter). When we started work we had penny the shilling. 'Course, there used to be four of them that went
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 If you wanted to go to the cinema or a concert or anywhere, did your parents give you the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, we used to go, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You didn't pay for it out of your pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, if we had it. If we had it we used to have to pay ourselves, but if we didn't have it 
they used to give it us. We didn't used to go so much, they weren't going then so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you get a bit of pocket money as a regular thing every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, about 3d. I got. I don't know how much the bigger ones got, about a shilling, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Apart from going to the concerts and such like, what would you spend your 3d. on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't know, I've no idea, now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You didn't try to save up for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you buy sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, but I can't remember now, what kind. No, I can't remember what we used to spend pocket money on, at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did anybody outside the home, apart from the washer woman do anything to help your mother to look after the home or the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You didn't have any relations, or friends and neighbours ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to all have our own jobs, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 If your mother was ill, or confined to bed, how did she manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 My father used to have to do it then. We used to all have to do our share, you know.
 She weren't ill so much, until she got old and then she had bronchitis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But you would manage amongst you to cope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I suppose you'd be too young to remember when the youngest member of the family was born, as to whether she had anybody in to help then?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I think you mentioned a relative who lived nearby, your father's sister it was, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, well she didn't live near to us. She lived the other end of the town altogether, she lived past the bridge. We lived up 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Great Lever Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. But she used to come ... she used to come to our house sometimes, you know, Sundays, sometimes, for a tea, and that. She was a big Chapel woman, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, Mother had two sisters living ... 3 sisters living, but they're all dead, now. And me father had a brother in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. I never saw him at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did these 3 sisters of your mother live near enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, they used to live in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose}, used to visit each other sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Frequently, or not so frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, not so frequently, perhaps about every 3 months or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And your parents would visit them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you would all go along as well, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Sometimes we did and sometimes we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about friend, would they have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, they had friends. But they didn't bring them to the house much, you know, they had friends, like, when they went out, I suppose, and relatives, but they didn't used to bring any friends with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Where would they see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, you see, perhaps when they went having a drink Saturday night. And perhaps when they went to some place where they'd be, you see. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And would your parents ever go to visit them in their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I should think so, but not often. They didn't used to visit so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents share their friends, or did your mother have some of her own and your father have some of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, me father didn't have ... it was me mother, really, that had these friends. You know, women. Me father didn't used to have many friends, that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were these friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Not that I know of. Me aunts, you know,
 me mother's sisters sometimes used to come. Have their tea, you know. In the week time sometimes they used to come, have their tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would people ever all in casually?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Only when invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 People often tell us that in tho
se days they used to make their own amusements. What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Me father used to go bowling. You know, he had friends there, round the park. And I don't think me mother eve
r went out doing anything, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they ever play games or have musical get-togethers with their friends, or were these just purely family affairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They were purely family affairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It's common to divide society into
 different social classes. In the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one social class and others to another social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Class, yes. Some were richer than the others. Well, there were always that, isn't there? Always that. Class, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What would you say the different social classes were? Before 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, there was always poor people, you know, that didn't work and couldn't get work, and ill and all that. Poor people. But we were never poor, you know what I me
an. Were never poor. We always got along. I think I told you they bought 2 houses, cash down and that helped a lot, you see. They used to get the rent and make a bit of profit on the rents and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What would you say that your class was, the class that your family belonged to? If you had to give a name to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
You mean poor? Well, I wouldn't say as we were poor. I wouldn't say as we was ever poor that I know of. Always had plenty to eat, and clothes and always went away for our holidays, and never our of work much that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But you probably wouldn't say that you were in the rich category?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Not rich, no, wouldn't say that we were rich, but to say 'are you well off' or something like that, you know. I wouldn't say that we was wel
l off, that means if you're rich. We weren't rich and we weren't poor, just got along. I dare say some people thought we were ... you know, had money and all that, but we didn't think about things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of people would you say belonged in the same category as you? In terms of either occupation, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
I don't know. We didn't bother with many friends, you see. Me mother used to ... me father had some friends who were always bosses, you know what I mean, overlookers, 
and me mother used to be friends with the wives, and that. They used to meet at parties, if they had any, and things like that, but ... Wouldn't call them rich.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were you ever told to curtsey to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Or were the boys taught to touch, or raise their cap to anybody if they met in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't think so, they were all ... lads, you know, football and cricket and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was there anybody that you had to call 'sir' or 'madam'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Not that I know of. I didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you remember whether anybody made any show of respect to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. We didn't used to think about those things, somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Who would be considered to be the most important people in the district? Or was it a district where everybody was treated much the same?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We were all treated alike, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about the clergy, or the teachers, or professional people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, they never used to come. Clergy never used to come, although we used to go, we never had a clergy come visiting. Not that I know of.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would you have any idea who people like the professional classes would associate with? You know,
 as their friends? The clergy, for instance, or the teachers, what sort of people they would associate with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, they used to keep to themselves, mostly, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The people like the overlookers would associate within your group. What about the employers, did you know any of the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. Mill owners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Mill owners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 None of them lived in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. You see, it was all mills then, you see, they were building new mills all the time, and, you see, people got wo
rk there, you see. Well, we were all, like, one class, all mill people. And the mill owners, well, they had the money to build the mills, so I suppose they lived somewhere outside of the towns, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They'd be more {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Chorley New Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 type of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Now, you went to Chapel, didn't you? You were a Wesleyan Chapel family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of people would go to your Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, well ... they were all working men, working people, like us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were there any richer ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No richer ones, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about the other denominations? Presumably there'd be a Church of England in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 St. Mark's, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And was there a Catholic Church around there, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, there was one or two ... St. Peter's and Paul's, and St. William's there is now, that was a new one, but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of people would go to those churches, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. We didn't live near those, you see, but ... it was in the area, but like, too far away for us to bother with th
em at all. More like poor people used to go to Catholic, more. They always seemed to be poor people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you know anybody who went to the Church, to St. Mark's, for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we didn't. I know they went to them, but I didn't know anything about them, you know, I didn't know anything about them, at all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You couldn't say what sort of people they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In your working class district some people were poor and some people were a bit better off, like your family. Would you say t
hat there were any other differences that you could make between the people in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were some considered to be respectable and others rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, well, there was 1 or 2, there's always like that, isn't there. One or 2 as were a bit rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was there a poorer family than yours that you knew that you can describe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, there's this washer woman, like, she was poor. Me mother used to help her. Me mother used to help people like that if they were poor. She
 used to lend money to them. They used to come and ask her, you know, if her'd lend them some money. Used to lend money a bit, but not for profit, like, you know. Used to do it to help them, they'd pay her back when they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did she ever find that people couldn't pay her back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, they used to come and they used to bring Co-Op cheques, would she like them'? you see, like that. Me father used to do a bit of that, too, when he was out collecting insurance, they couldn't pay him sometimes when 
he went and they asked him, would he have this and would he have that instead of money; cheques, Co-Op cheques, and little bits of things around the house, you know, would he take them if they'd be any good to him if they couldn't pay him. He lost more mo
ney than he drew, in fact.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would he take these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Sometimes. Sometimes he wouldn't bother, he used to let it run on, you know, pay him when they could. There was all that kind of thing, you know, going then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The washer woman was very poor, was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, she had a husband that was always off ill, always off his work, you know, he had a bad heart, or something ... bad heart, I think, and he was always off his work ill, you see. She hadn't many children, only about 2 or 3, but she u
sed to do a bit of washing to get a bit of money, you see, to help her husband out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would that family perhaps be a bit short of food and such like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, I can't tell you that, I don't know. Mother used to give her a parcel when she give her money
, you know, she used to give her things, clothes, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Would you say that any of the groups felt superior to the others? Considering your mother and the washer woman, do you think your mother would feel that she was in a superior category to the washer woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your mother and father have the same attitude towards people in all the different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. Never used to hear any arguments at all about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Your mother and father were not sort of class conscious at all, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. Not that I know of, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was it possible at all in that time, in that district to move from one social class to another? You know, to rise in the world, and so on?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would you say, for instance, that your own father did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you mean when he took this insurance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, or by virtue of earning enough to be able to buy these other houses. Would you say that that was sort of a change of class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, it was like a bit of a built-up for him, he alw
ays had that to fall back on, you see. They had the rents, and they always had that coming in. And then we went and had a bigger house when we was growing up, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 So that your own standard of living improved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But you don't think you specially moved out of one class into another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no. We were always working people, we didn't think we was rich or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you remember anybody locally being described as 'a real gentleman' or 'a real lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well
, I hadn't thought about it then, you see, I didn't think about it. You see, we hadn't enough money, and rich people, you see, it's drummed into them, isn't it, about other people being rich and they must look up to them and things like that, but when you
're not rich you don't seem to bother about things like that. We didn't look up to anybody, you know, like ... better than us, we didn't look up to anybody like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you didn't look down on anybody either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we just lived our own life, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They used to walk about, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you think about them? Were you afraid, or not bothered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We didn't used to come in contact with them, tell you the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your mother or father ever threaten you when you were naughty, as a small child, that they'd call the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you ever see anything of the landlord that you rented your home from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, well, they belonged to the railways, you see. They belonged to the rail - what were they called, then? I think it were the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lancashire{\*\xmlclose} and Yorkshire Railway Company, I think that was it, and it belonged to them. They used to have some liens at the top of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Challing Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, used to be sleepers, and then railway lines run across, you see, and that was belonging to the Lancashire }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362178 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  Yorkshire trains. Well, that was the land, you see, that they'd bought and had these houses put on, you see. And that was it, they belonged to 
the ... all those houses along, they belonged to the railway company. I don't know whether they do yet or not, but they're still up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What were the arrangements about collecting the rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, well, they used to have an agent, you know, used to come every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you feel about the railway company as a landlord? If you wanted anything doing was it done without much bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no, you used to have to wait, you know, wait your turn, and all that. But they used to decorate them and paint them and all that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They weren't so bad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, they weren't really bad. They weren't really bad as to say they wouldn't do anything, but ... they used to decorate for you and paint the houses and she what wanted doing. I suppose you had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 wait}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  your turn or something like that, but they used to do them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, they might have, but I don't know about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did it make any difference at all during the peri
od your father was out of work, the period after he'd given up spinning and before he had the insurance round? Or did it make any difference if he was off ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Can't remember him being ill at all. Can't remember him once being ill. Only when he was o
lder, when he was 70, and things like that, but I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You were never sufficiently short of money to need to get help yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, not that I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were you ever given lessons by either your father or mother, or a governess, or anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Don't know. About 5, I should think. I don't think you went to school before you was 5.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It varies, some people think they went to school earlier, but you think it was 5?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes. I think ... me elder brothers have said, you know, they went when they was 3. And you had to pay a penny. School money, they used to call it. I remember that, what they used to talk about, you see, but I went to this Claredon Street School and th
at wasn't built when me eldest brothers ... they went to a little school in Steel Street, and then they built this Claredon Street and then we all went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What kind of a school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, a big one, it's there yet, it's quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was it a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, it was a ... what do they call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 A Council School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 A Board School. What they call Board School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And it would be a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were there boys and girls in the same classes, or ... they weren't segregated into different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It were half girls and half boys.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Within the class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What time in the morning did you ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Until ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Four, was it? I don't know. About 4, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, we had dinner time, something similar than it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you go home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, we went home. We all went home to our dinners, 'cos they didn't provide them then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We used to go ... there's a park, I don't know whether you know it or not but it's in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Ridgeman Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, it's called {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Haywood{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Well, we used to ... {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Channing Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} is ... what shall I say? There's {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lever Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and then {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Channing Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}'s off {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lever Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Well we used to have to go through {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lever Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and up another Street called {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Olding Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and then the park. We used to go through the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How long would it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, not long, about 10 minutes. We used to run, you know. Som
etimes we wouldn't go through the park, we'd go, like, through the streets, but oftener than not we'd go through the park if it was find and light and all like that. We could go through the park. Didn't take us long, and then just across the road ... Clar
edon Street School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did anybody go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, we used to be a ... you know, children, there used to be ... I don't know, 3 or 4 of us used to go together, you see, from home. And then children from the other houses, you know, we used to meet
 them and come home together. We didn't have mothers coming for us then, they didn't come at the playtime, either, with anything. We used to always go on our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, we used to like going. Used to like going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Different ones, I suppose ... There was one, a Miss Hobson, she used to grind her teeth, you know, and give you a smack if you didn't do things. But I never were one that got smacked or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your teachers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 emphasize}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  particular things, like manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, they used to teach us, you know, what ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about punctuality, were they strict on that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, yes, we had to be all the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What about your way of speaking, did they bother about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, we used to have to read, you see, they'd teach you how to read, you had to read aloud, and that was the way that they taught you how to talk properly and all, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 If any of the children did do something that the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Used to get caned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they used any other form of punishment at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 This Miss Hobson, she used to smack you, you know. Smack your face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they ever make you stand in the corner, or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, not that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It was always either a caning or a smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of offences would they get that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, if you did anything wrong, or if you w
ere talking, you know, in the class. And if you did your sums wrong, or your composition, they used to call it, writing, you know, wrong, and if you did it too bad well, you got a smack then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would girls get the same punishment as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, they didn't used to come, you know, there used to be enough of us, they had ... They knew it all, you know, all talking different about school. They didn't used to come or anything like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they ask you what you'd been doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, yes. They used to say 'what have your learned'. We were all pretty good scholars, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did they ever meet your teachers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did the other children attending the school come from similar kinds of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would the teachers ever single out some of the children for different treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, not that I know of.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were there any gangs in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, no gangs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were there any children who seemed to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to all play together in the school yard. That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You just went to this one school, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you know how old you were when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I was 11.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You left altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would you have stayed on longer if you could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, no, they used to have what they call labour examinations then and if you passed when you was 11 you'd go a working. So I went in for that, you know. I 
went in without telling me mother and father, I wanted to go a working, I don't know why. I wanted to be earning a bit of something, and I went in for this exam and I passed, so I went and got a job on me own, and that was it. Oh, well it was 11 - you had
 to be 11 - and it was 12 when I left, full time, either 12 or 13, I'm not sure, when you was full time, they used to call it, working full time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You mean would were working part time between the ages of 11 and 12 or 13?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No. I wonder sometimes was made me go in for this exam, you know, but one or two of the girls had been in for it and so I wanted to do the same thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Looking back do you think that ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I might have done (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, we used to read and write and sew and cook and ... oh, yes, we used to ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You used to do all that at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you ever attend any part time classes after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Dressmaking. I once went to a dressmaking class. Night school, that was at Church Institute. It's not a school now, is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Is this {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Silverwell Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, at the bottom there. I went there, dressmaking class. Miss Osman was the teacher.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well now, you were working as a half timer. You were working in the morning, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, one week, and afternoons the next week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you were at school the other half of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Where was this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Oh, it was ... do you know weaving? They have what they call yells at back of the looms. Have you seen them? Have you ever seen a weaving ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, I have, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4795782\charrsid10836950 They have what they call yeld}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 s, you know, the threads like this. Well
, I went to a place where they made these yells. Horrockses Heald Shop they used to call it, and I was there 'till I was about ... oh, yes, well I left when I was full time there. I weren't making enough money. Only used to get two shillings a week.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What hours did you have to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Used to go in a morning, early, six o'clock until dinnertime, 12 o'clock, I think it was. And the afternoons you went 1 o'clock 'till half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I see, so one week you'd be working from 6 'till 12 in the morn
ing and went to school in the afternoon, and the other week you'd be going to school in the morning and working from one 'till half past five. What about Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Two shillings the week! Saturdays? I don't ... yes, we used to have to work every other Saturday. We used to work 'till one o'clock.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did you think about this 2/- a week, did you think it was a fair ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It was just 'cos I wanted to go aworking, I didn't think about the 2/-. And then when I went full time I didn't think I wa
s getting enough money, so they was getting more in the cotton mills, then, so ... oh, they were wanting them all over the place, you could get going and get a job any time, so I went in and got one, full time, in the card room - used to call it the card 
room, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Before you went on to your full time job, though, while you were still at Horrockses what exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, they called it reaching, they called it ... you wouldn't understand it. These yells, the lady was s
at in a chair here and you sat lower down and you used to give her these stitches, you had them on your had, get them like this, and she used to gather them up in the bobbin and knit them, you see, put them over this thing. That was all you did, sit down 
all the time giving her these stitches. They used to call it yelding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 This was in the weaving shed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, it wasn't a weaving shed, it was just where they made these yelds, and they had these stitches on a long frame and you'd pick these stitches u
p and give them to the other person that was sat on this chair, and she kind of wound it round and put it on a frame. That was the yell, what they call the yeld. It was h, e, a, l, d, but they called it yeld, they used to call it. But it wasn't hard work,
 in fact it was too easy, really, they were sat there all the time, that's all they had to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It was a sort of mechanical process that ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, they were just sat there all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Your two shillings that you earned, did you think it was a fair wage for what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
I gave it to me mother, anyhow, I gave it to me mother. Oh, yes, they carried on to me about it. And me brother, me eldest brother, oh, he went on, he wanted me mother to make me stop it, you know, make me go ba
ck to school, but I wouldn't you know, I just wanted to stay there, then. As I said I've been working ever since, until I got me pension.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your mother give you the penny in the shilling back out of this 2 shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, twopence. Twopence extra, that was beside what they used to give us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Besides your normal pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What was the money spent on? You know, the money that you gave to your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, I don't know, it all went in the family budget, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you get on with the other people who worked at Horrockses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you come into contact much with the other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, yes, I'd got some friends there. In fact one of them was there when I was there and she went to be
 a midwife and she came to me first baby. And the second one. I had two children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did the employer at Horrockses treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, he was all right. He was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What did you feel about the work? Interest, or bored?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I used to just go, that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you actually like it, or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
I suppose I must have liked it or else I wouldn't have stayed, would I? But it were just coming out of the school, I suppose, like the other children. We didn't used to bother, you see. Pass this exam. You had to pass this exam to leave school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did having this job alter your attitude towards school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Older, you know, I felt older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did it affect the way you approached the school work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have any other part time jobs at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. I just went on the cotton mill, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You then went on to carding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you go to one firm and stay with that one firm all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, I went to one firm and I stayed there 'till I was 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Which firm was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 That was Ainsworth in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Western Street{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. I think they've pulled that down, now. And then me mother was ill one time and I used to stay home to look after her. Well, she was ill ... she had bronch
itis and she was very ill, so I stayed home and I went and asked one of my friends would she tell the boss, you know, that I couldn't come in as me mother was ill. Well, she never told him, she forgot, she said, so when I was off he said word that I hadn'
t
 to go back again, you know, 'cos I'd stayed off without telling them, without sending word, so they wouldn't. .... I told him that I'd sent word with the girl. She worked there, but she forgot to tell him, but he wouldn't take any notice then, you see, h
e thought I was just telling a tale, and that, but it was right. So I went to Wolfenden's, a lot nicer firm and stayed there 'till I was married. Thirty, I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you were doing the same job, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Still in carding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, not carding. It was called a card room, but it was on frames. Carders, the men do that. Carders, the men do that work, with the cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What exactly did you have to do at Ainsworth's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, what they call setting on, then, used to have to put
 the bobbins on the spindles, you know. Empty bobbins, take the full ones off, put the empty ones on. And that was till you got a frame of your own, and then you watched this frame, you see, and you got a setter on. So I got a frame, I had 2 frames when I
 were ... oh, years I had two frames.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have 2 frames when you were at Ainsworth's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, no, just ... I went on what they call boxes, and ... you see, there're different processes in the cardroom. They come off the cards and they go in a tin
 round like that, well that goes into what ... boxing. I forget what they call it now, boxes or something like that, and that goes on a bobbin. Well, I went on one of those, you go on one that one after being setter on you go on this card, this ... the bo
x
es, and then you go on another frame that comes off this boxing frame and they you go on to jack frames, you see, you go up like that. Well, I was what they call a box tenter and I got what when I went to Wolfenden's and then I got promoted 'till I got tw
o frames, you see. So that's the highest you can get, really, in the cardroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 When you were at Ainsworth's what hours did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Six o'clock in the morning 'till half past 5, and then it dropped to 5 o'clock, you know, the hours went shorter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 While you were still at Ainsworth's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No? After you'd gone to Wolfenden's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 At Wolfenden's, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You would have a dinner break?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, an hour. And half an hour at breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What was that, 8 o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, 8 o'clock 'till half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You used to take something in with you, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, sometime we went home because we weren't far away. Sometimes we went home and sometimes we had our lunch in the works, we used to get hot water from the hous
es opposite, they used to serve hot water, and we used to take our tea and sugar, and you have hot water, tea, and we used to go back to the mill and have it in the mill. All the machinery was stopped, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you take the food from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was this for breakfast? And sometimes for dinner, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we used to go home for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You went home, for dinner, but you had this sort of arrangement for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. We used to have sandwiches, mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have any holidays, by the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, we went ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The Monday to Thursday, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, that was ... then they had a week, after, you know, they went in for a week's holiday, so we had a week. We had Whitsuntide about 4 days and a week in June, then we had Good Friday and Monday, and we had Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were these paid or unpaid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no, they weren't paid. They were unpaid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 At both places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What were you paid when you were at Ainsworth's, what did you start at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We started at 7/6d. a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did it go up at all while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, it kept going up until I got ... 35/- I think were the highest I got, at Wolfenden's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was the rate of pay you got at Wolfenden's when you were a box tenter the same as it was when you were a box tenter at Ainsworth's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The firms paid pretty well the same wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, they did. What you made, you see, on these frames, these two frames, you got what you made and you had a kind of clock on your machine, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 A piece work sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, yes, you got what you made, you see, paid what you made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you feel that it was a fair wage for what wages were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I think so then, yes. It was very nice work. You know, clean and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you go on giving the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, gave it to 'till I was married. I got five shillings then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you get on with the other people who worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 All right, I had some good friends, we used to have some nice ... yo
u know, outings and all like that. There's always one or two as can't .... you know, get on with at both places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You said that you liked it at Wolfenden's better than at Ainsworth's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, well, it was a big ... it were more roomy, you know, it w
ere more modern. It was a bigger place. It hadn't been up as long as Ainsworth's, and it was lighter and more room, you know, pleasanter, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did the employers treat you? At Ainsworth's this man who sort of sacked you because you ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Ye
s, yes, he was the carder ... I don't know who it was, he just simply said, you know, he wasn't having that kind of thing. But I was ... you know, told him that I'd told this girl, and I went to her and asked her why she didn't tell him, she said oh, she 
forgot. Just like that ... forgot. And he wouldn't take that as an excuse. He felt I were making it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, I felt very upset about it. I didn't know what to do then, I didn't know whether to go back in the mill or not.
 Me brother didn't want me to go back in the mill, and ... anyhow, it was all that I knew, you see, so I got a place there. I just went to see if they wanted anybody and they took me on, and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you feel about the work itself, first of all when you were at Ainsworth's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, it was all right, you just did it. That was all, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you like it, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, I liked it, but after I got to Wolfenden's I could see the difference, you see, it was a lot p
leasanter. The boss was pleasanter, too. You see, all round it was better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You felt you were treated better there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, more .... everything was more open, more room and more light and all that, you see, very pleasant, more pleasant. Of course,
 Ainsworth's was an old mill they'd been there years. I think it's pulled down, now. There's one been pulled down, they had two mills. One, I think, I don't know whether the other has or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 The job at Wolfendens, this being a fairly new mill, did they have any special welfare arrangements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No. They used to have what they call watch houses, you know, where you go in at the door. Well, you used to go in there if there was anything wrong with you. Any accidents, you went in there and they used to 
attend to you. There was no special person, like. Except one that was, like, the boss. The head one in the watch house, they used to attend to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 They would render first aid, and such like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Have you done any jobs at all since the first World War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 'Cos you married in 1918 and you stopped working then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Looking back, would you have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 preferred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, I might have done if I'd've been better educated, you know. If I'd've gone to any classes and so on, but you just did it, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of thing to you think you might have liked to have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't know. I went in for dressmaking once, you know, I went to classes. I don't know whether I had one or two sess
ions, winter sessions. But I told ... you see, all the others were getting married, you know, as I got older. All the others were getting married and I was the one at home, I was the ... well, me younger brother, of course, he went to the war, and ... But
 
after the war he got married and, you see, I was the one left, so ... No, he didn't, I got married before him. He sent word he was going to be married and I sent word to him as I was going to be married, so he didn't get married 'cos I was being married. 
So I got married before him and then he came home and he got married. So that was it. That was 1918. My husband, you know, him that I married, he was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose} and he had a job in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} that ... transport, belonged to the transport. He was ... got working 
on some horses and he came home in a boat that was bringing horses to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. So that was it, he didn't go back again, he stayed. So that was it, you see, we got married. He used to go out with my brother, before he went to Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Just to finish off the questions about your own working life; did you have to serve any apprenticeship or training }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 period}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  for either of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We had to be, yes, in the cardroom. The Cardroom Association.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you take a part in its activities?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. You just paid your money and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did it ever bring you out on strike or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. They wanted to go on strike because I got promoted, you see, when I went to Wolfenden's, you see,
 I got promoted and they thought I shouldn't've been promoted because I'd only just gone. You see, there was some more there before me thought I shouldn't've been and they were going to go out on strike. It didn't come to anything, the boss talked to them
 and all that. But that was the only thing (laughter), they going out on strike because I'd been promoted, you know, before the others that were there before me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did that incident affect your relationships with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, well, it did a bit, but 
they got over it. it was all right, it didn't come to anything. There was one of them, you know, the boss and she weren't having it, she was going out and she tried to get all the others to go out and the boss had them all in the office and talked to them
. So they all came trailing back again. Didn't make any difference (laughter). And he said to me 'carry on, carry on', he said, 'don't take any notice, they'll come round'. So that's it, that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you feel that the employers and the workers had the same interests? Or had they different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What do you mean, in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose} or outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, no. They all had their own lives, you know. Didn't bother with them much outside the mill, you know, just had your own friends.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were there good relations between the Union and the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 There might have been, but there's all kinds, you know, isn't there? All kinds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you feel that there was a distinction felt between the trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. You see, you all had to go through the same ... you started the lowest job and then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  got promoted, you see, as you went on, so there was no really apprenticeship, you know what I mean. You just did the work and then got promoted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you think that your fulltime work has changed your general attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Might have done, don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well now, after you'd left school and started to go to wo
rk you continued to live at home until you were married. Did the fact of your starting work change your relationship with your parents at all, or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, just getting other, that was all there was to it, you see. Your life changes as you get older.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you spend your Sunday any differently, or did you go on going to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, we just kept on going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 To Chapel and Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you develop an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you hold particular views? I mean, did you support a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, me father was a Liberal, like I told you. Well, we was all supposed to be Liberal after that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Because your father was, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, we heard him ta
lking, you know, and all that. Well, when you go to work and you join the trade union, you see, well, you ... like, you change your views then, you see, you vote Labour, you're supposed to be a Labour then, because you're in the trade union, so ... Well, 
this ... my husband, part of his life as I'm going to tell you, but that changed my politics. When he was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose} he learned ... When he was in Bolton before he went to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} he was a musician, he learned ... pianist, he was a good piano player and he us
ed to learn under ... was it Percy Rigby at the Victoria Hall? Not Percy. What was his name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I'm afraid I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, he was at the Victoria Hall, he was the conductor ... orchestra, and a good pianist. Well, he learned under him. Well, he
 passed all his exams and he could be a teacher, he could have been a teacher. Well, they had some trouble at home, his mother, she was a bit ... you know, funny. Then they all left home, at their house, and he went to Canada and while he was there he too
k
 any job that was going because he'd been thinking about going in the profession, teaching music - he was a lovely pianist - and he took any job ... first job that came to him 'till he got going. And he was going something on a machine and he his thumb ta
k
en off, right down there like that. Couldn't play the piano, then, and he couldn't reach his octaves, like, you know. And that squashed his piano playing. Well, he learnt plastering then. He was living with someone that was a master plasterer, and they we
r
e all sorry for him, like, when he lost his thumb, so he said he'd teach him ... he'd learn him how to be a plasterer. So he took it on ... first job that came up, he took it on. He he learned, served his apprenticeship ... they only had to serve 4 years 
in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Well, here they had to serve 7 years, see. Well, he came home - I told you he was in the transport when the war was on ... when the war broke out he was there. And he came home ... he came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, well, they wouldn't have him in the Army, you
 see because he had this thumb. So he thought he'd start plastering, you see, so he got a job ... they were wanting them, they were building houses, you know Corporation houses all over the place, and they got to know that he hadn't served his time in Eng
l
and, these trades union fellows and they came to him and they said he couldn't work here, and why was that, because he'd learned it in Canada, he'd not learned it here. So everywhere he went they blacked him. Couldn't get work, so he started on his own. A
nd he joined the Masters Federation. And they wouldn't work for him then. They blacked him then because he'd worked in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and not served his time here. So that changed my attitude. I'll never vote Labour again as long as I live. It broke his heart, you know. Couldn't get work at all, until the Masters Federation Secretary - I forget what his name is now, they're at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and he got to know about it. My husband, Earnie, went to him and told him all about it. So he said he fight the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose} for him and
 he'd make them recognize him, you see. And he did. He took them to Court and he won the case. That was the secretary of the Masters Federation. Well, they had to let him work then, and he was all right after.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How long did all this go on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, well, that was when we got married. We got married when he came home from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and he could get work then, you see. But they followed him about, so where he got work, if he didn't stop work they'd all come off. Terrible, isn't it. And he had to stop
 work, you see. Anyway, the Secretary said he'd fight the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}
, they weren't going to do that. So they did, and they had to recognize him. So he was in the Masters Federation, then he kept on his own, got his own. He was 70. Master plasterer. But he had a
 hard job, you know. Every night when he came home, walked about the bedroom, couldn't sleep, how to get the better of them, you know, how to get them to ... So that finished me with Labour. I mean, to tray and stop a man ... and they were wanting plaster
ers. Wouldn't let him work at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would you vote in the 1918 election? That was the first one that women could vote at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I voted Liberal. Yes, I was Liberal. I kept to me own Liberal you know, because you were supposed to be a trade unionist to v
ote Labour, but I didn't. I voted Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you feel under any pressure to vote, either because of your employers or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, it was because of that, it changed my attitude altogether. When he come home to you like that, you k
now, it makes you feel they're trying to ruin your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 life for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950  you, you know, don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way when you started to work, or did you do different sorts of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 With my husband, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, before you were married. You know, from being about 14 to when you did get married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I used to do a lot of crocheting, and knitting, and all that, you know. Used to go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But after you left school, did you carry on doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you go out in the evening much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, the pictures were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15270502\charrsid10836950 going then}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 . Used to go to the cinema sometimes, the Hippodrome. Used to go to the Hippodrome a lot. About once a week, anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, you know, I 
used to go on me own more than anything. I used to go out with a girl and she started going out with a boy, so I went on me own. I used to go on me own mostly, 'till I started going with a ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you make any new friends when you started work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Do you mean in the cardroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, yes. Nice lot of people they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you make any special friends that you would bring home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, not as I'd go out with, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents meet any of your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, yes
, we used to take them. You know, the nice ... me friend that I used to go out with regular because she used to go to school, you know, like I did. Used to bring her to our house to her tea and I used to go to their house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents expect to k
now where you were, after you left school and were working. If you went out in the evening, did they expect to know where you were and did they expect you back at a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We used to tell them, I suppose. We didn't used to bother about that
. We used to tell them where we were going, that was it, you see, we would say where we was going. They didn't used to bother about what time we went in, but we didn't used to stay out late so they had no need to bother. We weren't like these, you know, g
oing out and staying out all night and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Now, you married in 1918 and your husband had been in Canada. You'd known him before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, he used to go out with my brother. Used to come to the house, used to play the piano and I the organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 That was how you met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 About how long had you known him, then, altogether, before you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 From about 16. About 16 years old. We used to go to the same school, you seem same Sunday School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did he come from Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you save up before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your parents help you to set up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, yes, they bought a table and bit of things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you move into a home of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, not at first. You see, I told you he was a plasterer. Well, he got a job in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham
{\*\xmlclose} ... that was before he went on his own, he thought he'd go out of town, you see, and he went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Well, that lasted 18 months. We got 2 rooms down there, a sittingroom and a bedr
oom and we stayed down ... I stayed with him 'till this job was finished. And then we came home, and one of these houses that I told you me mother and father had came empty, so we just walked in it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How long were you in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How long were you engaged before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, well, I'd known him a long time, you see, and he came home from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, we just went out together and then got married. Not long, about 12 months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Could you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
We didn't have a big wedding, if that's what you mean, we just went to the Victoria Weslyan Chapel, got married in the morning, because I was 30 years old, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have many guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We had about 6, that was all. Six or 8.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Quite a small private affair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, it was a private wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How about wedding presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, we got quite a few, but ... you know, they kept coming in by degrees. You see, we hadn't ... we had it at home, you see, the reception, we didn't hav
e it at any place. We got different presents off people, they kept coming in, you know, after the wedding. You see, we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. That's when we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, after we got married. And when we was married we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, you see, straight away, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have a honeymoon before you went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, only about 3 days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How old was your husband when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 He was same age as me., 30.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You went to Birmingham just for 18 months. That was really after the end of 1918, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Or was it during 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, we got married in September 1918. Well, we went to Birmingham about September 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\super\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 , 1918. And after that he worked on his own, started on his own here in Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How much of the money your husband earned would he give you? Do you know how you much he earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, he used to get ... used to have to wait 'till his bills came in, you see. Used to have to wait of them paying him, you see, and he used to have a lot of money out, you see, he used to give it me when he got it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But did you have a fair idea of how much he was earning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, yes. Well, he used to give me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362178 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 5 at the beginning, and then after he ... Of course, he used to pay the bills
, you know, too, he used to always buy me something. I never bought any stockings or any gloves or shoes. He used to buy all my things. Always bringing me things home, like. Oh, I've nothing to grumble about according to the money, it was all mine if he h
ad it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you discuss together how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, he used to say ... you know, I was the money ... I used to mind the money for him, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 When you went to Birmingham you had these rooms. This was only a temporary arrangements, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You wouldn't have anybody else living ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, there was an old lady there, but she was the landlady of the house, you know. She lived in the back place, we had the front, like.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you do the domestic duties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, I used to help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes. And I used to make him his dinners and take them, it wasn't so far off where he worked, and I used to take his dinners, see. Used to make his dinners and take them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Only me own. I didn't used to do hers, only me own, and kept the room tidy where we lived, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you make or mend any of the clothes that you and your husband wore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Used to mend his socks (laughter). Yes, I used to mend his things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you do much buying of clothes when you were in Birmingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, I had plenty of clothes, you see, and I got a new outfit when I was married, you see. And it was only 18 months, so I had plenty of clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did your husband help at all with the domestic jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, because there were two of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And for meals, you used to take his dinner out to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You just had one room, didn't you, where you would eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you did you cooking...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 She had a cooker and I used to do it ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In the lady's kitchen, you didn't have one of your own?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. It was 3 rooms, you know, sitting room, diningroom and this kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you do much cooking there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, I used to make a cake and make puddings, and make a proper dinner. And then I used to cook his tea, sometimes, fish, and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Were your meals pretty much the same as you'd been used to all your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, yes, at home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you do anything like making bread or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, didn't make bread, no. I used to bake bread when we came to Bolton and got a house. I used to bake bread there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Was the money coming in reasonably at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, it was a bit of a struggle, you see. His mother ... his father died, he was only 58, I think, h
is father. Well, he had some property and they weren't without money. Well, when his mother died this property were divided between them, you see, so my husband ... I think they all had about 6 houses each, they had a lot of property. He had 6 houses, so 
what he did was sold them, these houses, and that set him up in business, you see, that made it that he could lie out on his money a bit longer, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 This was after you came back to Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 But when you were first married and living in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, you had a bit of a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 His wages, yes. He worked for a firm, you see, he went aworking for a firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 A plastering ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes. So we saved up. I saved up, I had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362178 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 30 when I came home, what I'd saved on the ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you go short on food at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
No, no, we never went short of food. We were never short of money like ... from hand to mouth, like that, but you see, like I told you, he had this property his father left and of course, it were all his mother's when his fat
her died, and then when she died it all separated and divided, you see, and he sold his. They were only little house, they weren't big houses and he sold them all and kept on with the plastering, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have any leisure time when you were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, plenty. We used to go out. We used to go to the pictures and the theatre. We went out a lot in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, because it wasn't our own house you see, and she was always there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have any activities in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 W
ell, he used to play the piano. And next door lady, she came in and asked him would he teach her son, she had a boy about 10, I think he was, and so he used to go in and learn him the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 While you were at Birmingham, did you take in any newspapers and magazines then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No magazines. Newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you have books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Well, no, we didn't used to read so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you belong to a library at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No. Well, we knew it was only temporary, you see, you don't join things like that so much, do you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 How did you spend holidays and bank holidays during that short period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We came home. Used to stay with me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And you used to go out quite a bit Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 We used to go watching the crick
et matches at Saturdays, and we used to go to the Hippodrome at night. And Sundays we used to go for a ride somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you go to Church or Chapel at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No, not then. That dropped it off for me, that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 And what about your husband politics? You told me about yours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, he wouldn't vote Labour, no. He'd vote Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Would he vote in 1918, would he be back in time to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you make any friends when you were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes. We was on rations 
then, you know, you had a ration book, so there was a shop at the top of the road where we lived there was a grocer's, and so he said, 'I'll take you to the shop', he said, and you had to register, you see, before you got any food. So I went up and oh, sh
e was nice, this person so she asked where we'd come from, and all that, so she had a sister that married a man from Blackpool, so she was quite used to this {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lancashire{\*\xmlclose}
 talk, you see. So she asked us to go up. Her husband was a singer, a tenor singer, and s
he asked us 'can you play the piano?' I said, 'well, me husband can'. 'Oh, well, come up, that's just what we want', so we used to go up, and made friends there. Used to go often, up. And her brother - she had some brothers - see, we had to go there, so w
e had more friends than what we could cope with because we couldn't ask them back so well, you know. We'd really more friends than what we'd bargained for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 You had quite a gay time in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 It was all right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Did you come into contact much with the people round about in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}
}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Well, we had a landlady and she had a sister-in-law that lived opposite, used to come in. and then we had this grocer's ... very nice family, they were, and they made you welcome, you know, and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 What sort of a district was it in Birmingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
It's opened out now. I believe there's all Corporation houses now up there where we used to live, but it was just on the outskirts of Smethwick.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 So it was quite a nice district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 
Yes, it was. It's built up now, we wouldn't know it if we went now, with Corporation houses ... Council houses all at the top where this grocer's shop is, they opened it out, you see, up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 At the time when you were there it was quite a good district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Yes, it was, it was respectable, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Who were the most important people there? Who would be considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Now do you mean, in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 In that part of the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 Oh, yes, well this la
dy where we lived, she was supposed to be important because she used to have an hotel there and she sold it when her husband died. She knew a lot of people. And then there was her sister-in-law. Well, that's all we knew, really, and this lady that had thi
s grocer's shop, you know, she was ... they had a nice business there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I was just trying to find out about the sort of community it was that you were living in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3306704 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 'Course, we didn't bother with them so much, you know, the neighbours, he was working
 out all day. I used to go shopping and ... It's a bit difficult going shopping, they don't know what you're talking about in some places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2912712 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003502\charrsid10836950 I don't think I'll carry on with any further questions there because you weren't in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} for very long. It's really more what happened in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} that we're more concerned about, I think.
\par }}